The paper deals with decoding in Gaussian channels with intersymbol interference (ISI), which is a topic in information theory and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses communication channels, which suggests that it could belong to cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper may fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with communication channels. The paper also discusses decoding rules, which could place it under cs.SI (Signal Processing). Finally, the paper proposes a universal decoding procedure, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
